Line is beautiful.

Debby was partinlly compensated on the absence of shopping when we

We had lunch at the fine Washington Hotel on the
porch overlooking the
Atlantie und its breakwater entrance to the Canal. Drove beck to the
Pacifie side, visited the ruins of old Panana City sacked by Morgan, had

BUT - one engine quit and we had to return.
Finally repairs were completed
and se again took off at 9:00 a.., elimbed up for a good view of the Canal,

There are several aotive volcanos near there which we flew over,
Ineluding that new one which grew out of a farerla pasture a few years ago

Landed at
Cuatemala City for refueling,
and now as I write, welve recroased the isthmus
